                " 14 UD Pelletron accelerator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Self-supporting foils of approximately 1-mg/cm**2 thick",
                "isotopically enriched to 97.8% for Nd-146, to 98.2% for",
                "Nd-148 and to 99.9% Sm-148, were used as targets."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " an Enge split-pole spectrometer."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PSSCN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Position-sensitive gas counter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*EN-RSL-FW*.The energy resolution for the experiments",
                " was approximately 50 keV full width at half maximum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Coupled-channels analysis."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "P-SPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.Normalization factors for converting",
                "inelastic scattering yields to absolute differential",
                "cross sections were determined by comparing elastic",
                "scattering yields at each angle to the differential",
                "cross sections for elastic scattering predicted by",
                "using Becchetti-Greenless optical model parameters.",
                "*By authors*.In Nd-146, Nd-148 and Sm-148 nuclei",
                "the 5- states are usually considered to be \"octupole",
                "coupled\" states arising from the coupling of the",
                " 2+ and 3- states. It is found that the differential",
                "cross sections for excitation of the 5- states are",
                "somewhat larger than would be expected for octupole",
                "coupled structure. This excess strength can be",
                "explained in terms of small admixtures of two",
                "quasiparticle excitations in the 5- states."
              ]
            }
          ],
